verses.text_plain: These are also proverbs of Solomon, which the men of Hezekiah king of Judah copied out.
verses.verse_html: 1These are also proverbs of Solomon, which the men of Hezekiah king of Judah copied out.

verses.text_plain: It is the glory of God to conceal a thing: but the honour of kings is to search out a matter.
verses.verse_html: 2It is the glory of God to conceal a thing: but the honour of kings is to search out a matter.

verses.text_plain: The heaven for height, and the earth for depth, and the heart of kings is unsearchable.
verses.verse_html:
3The heaven for height, and the earth for depth, and the heart of kings is unsearchable. ▼
▼ is…: Heb. there is no searching

footnotes.body_text: ▼ is…: Heb. there is no searching
footnotes.body_html: ▼ is…: Heb. there is no searching

verses.text_plain: Take away the dross from the silver, and there shall come forth a vessel for the finer.
verses.verse_html: 4Take away the dross from the silver, and there shall come forth a vessel for the finer.

verses.text_plain: Take away the wicked from before the king, and his throne shall be established in righteousness.
verses.verse_html: 5Take away the wicked from before the king, and his throne shall be established in righteousness.

verses.text_plain: Put not forth thyself in the presence of the king, and stand not in the place of great men:
verses.verse_html:
6Put not forth thyself in the presence of the king, and stand not in the place of great men: ▼
▼ Put…: Heb. Set not out thy glory

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Put…: Heb. Set not out thy glory
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Put…: Heb. Set not out thy glory

verses.text_plain: For better it is that it be said unto thee, Come up hither; than that thou shouldest be put lower in the presence of the prince whom thine eyes have seen.
verses.verse_html: 7For better it is that it be said unto thee, Come up hither; than that thou shouldest be put lower in the presence of the prince whom thine eyes have seen.

tokens.text: hither; than that thou shouldest be put lower

verses.text_plain: Go not forth hastily to strive, lest thou know not what to do in the end thereof, when thy neighbour hath put thee to shame.
verses.verse_html: 8Go not forth hastily to strive, lest thou know not what to do in the end thereof, when thy neighbour hath put thee to shame.

verses.text_plain: Debate thy cause with thy neighbour himself; and discover not a secret to another:
verses.verse_html:
9Debate thy cause with thy neighbour himself; and discover not a secret to another: ▼
▼ a secret…: or, the secret of

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a secret…: or, the secret of
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a secret…: or, the secret of

verses.text_plain: Lest he that heareth it put thee to shame, and thine infamy turn not away.
verses.verse_html: 10Lest he that heareth it put thee to shame, and thine infamy turn not away.

verses.text_plain: A word fitly spoken is like apples of gold in pictures of silver.
verses.verse_html:
11A word fitly spoken is like apples of gold in pictures of silver. ▼
▼ fitly…: Heb. spoken upon his wheels

footnotes.body_text: ▼ fitly…: Heb. spoken upon his wheels
footnotes.body_html: ▼ fitly…: Heb. spoken upon his wheels

verses.text_plain: As an earring of gold, and an ornament of fine gold, so is a wise reprover upon an obedient ear.
verses.verse_html: 12As an earring of gold, and an ornament of fine gold, so is a wise reprover upon an obedient ear.

verses.text_plain: As the cold of snow in the time of harvest, so is a faithful messenger to them that send him: for he refresheth the soul of his masters.
verses.verse_html: 13As the cold of snow in the time of harvest, so is a faithful messenger to them that send him: for he refresheth the soul of his masters.

verses.text_plain: Whoso boasteth himself of a false gift is like clouds and wind without rain.
verses.verse_html:
14Whoso boasteth himself of a false gift is like clouds and wind without rain. ▼
▼ of a…: Heb. in a gift of falsehood

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of a…: Heb. in a gift of falsehood
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of a…: Heb. in a gift of falsehood

verses.text_plain: By long forbearing is a prince persuaded, and a soft tongue breaketh the bone.
verses.verse_html: 15By long forbearing is a prince persuaded, and a soft tongue breaketh the bone.

verses.text_plain: Hast thou found honey? eat so much as is sufficient for thee, lest thou be filled therewith, and vomit it.
verses.verse_html: 16Hast thou found honey? eat so much as is sufficient for thee, lest thou be filled therewith, and vomit it.

tokens.text: for thee, lest thou be filled

verses.text_plain: Withdraw thy foot from thy neighbour’s house; lest he be weary of thee, and so hate thee.
verses.verse_html:
17Withdraw thy foot from thy neighbour’s house; lest he be weary of thee, and so hate thee. ▼
▼ Withdraw…: or, Let thy foot be seldom in
 , ▼
▼ weary…: Heb. full of thee

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Withdraw…: or, Let thy foot be seldom in
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Withdraw…: or, Let thy foot be seldom in
▼ weary…: Heb. full of thee

verses.text_plain: A man that beareth false witness against his neighbour is a maul, and a sword, and a sharp arrow.
verses.verse_html: 18A man that beareth false witness against his neighbour is a maul, and a sword, and a sharp arrow.

verses.text_plain: Confidence in an unfaithful man in time of trouble is like a broken tooth, and a foot out of joint.
verses.verse_html: 19Confidence in an unfaithful man in time of trouble is like a broken tooth, and a foot out of joint.

verses.text_plain: As he that taketh away a garment in cold weather, and as vinegar upon nitre, so is he that singeth songs to an heavy heart.
verses.verse_html: 20As he that taketh away a garment in cold weather, and as vinegar upon nitre, so is he that singeth songs to an heavy heart.

verses.text_plain: If thine enemy be hungry, give him bread to eat; and if he be thirsty, give him water to drink:
verses.verse_html: 21If thine enemy be hungry, give him bread to eat; and if he be thirsty, give him water to drink:

verses.text_plain: For thou shalt heap coals of fire upon his head, and the Lord shall reward thee.
verses.verse_html: 22For thou shalt heap coals of fire upon his head, and the Lord shall reward thee.

verses.text_plain: The north wind driveth away rain: so doth an angry countenance a backbiting tongue.
verses.verse_html:
23The north wind driveth away rain: so doth an angry countenance a backbiting tongue. ▼
▼ driveth…: or, bringeth forth rain: so doth a backbiting tongue an angry countenance

footnotes.body_text: ▼ driveth…: or, bringeth forth rain: so doth a backbiting tongue an angry countenance
footnotes.body_html: ▼ driveth…: or, bringeth forth rain: so doth a backbiting tongue an angry countenance

verses.text_plain: It is better to dwell in the corner of the housetop, than with a brawling woman and in a wide house.
verses.verse_html: 24It is better to dwell in the corner of the housetop, than with a brawling woman and in a wide house.

verses.text_plain: As cold waters to a thirsty soul, so is good news from a far country.
verses.verse_html: 25As cold waters to a thirsty soul, so is good news from a far country.

verses.text_plain: A righteous man falling down before the wicked is as a troubled fountain, and a corrupt spring.
verses.verse_html: 26A righteous man falling down before the wicked is as a troubled fountain, and a corrupt spring.

verses.text_plain: It is not good to eat much honey: so for men to search their own glory is not glory.
verses.verse_html: 27It is not good to eat much honey: so for men to search their own glory is not glory.

verses.text_plain: He that hath no rule over his own spirit is like a city that is broken down, and without walls.
verses.verse_html: 28He that hath no rule over his own spirit is like a city that is broken down, and without walls.
